headline: Cintas-Targeted Uniform Supplier UniFirst Reports Mixed Q1 Results; Adjusts Annual Revenue Outlook
summary: UniFirst Corporation (NYSE:UNF) shares are trading higher after the company reported first-quarter results. Quarterly sales of $604.91 million missed the analyst consensus of $606.62 million. UniFirst registered an operating income of $55.5 million, an increase of 4.5% year over year. Adjusted EBITDA increased to $94.0 million from $88.7 million in the prior year. Adjusted EPS of $2.40 beat the consensus of $2.22.
